                <h1>Why Employers Conduct Background Checks</h1>
                <p>Jobs conduct background checks to ensure the safety and security of their workplace. These checks help employers verify a candidate's criminal history, employment record, and educational qualifications. By doing so, companies can reduce risks, protect their reputation, and foster a trustworthy environment, ultimately enhancing overall hiring decisions.</p>
